T*('Happy, master?' I cried.  'Strange happiness!  If you would hear me)Tj
T*(without being angry, I might offer some advice that would make you)Tj
T*(happier.')Tj
T*()Tj
T*('What is that?' he asked.  'Give it.')Tj
T*()Tj
T*('You are aware, Mr. Heathcliff,' I said, 'that from the time you were)Tj
T*(thirteen years old you have lived a selfish, unchristian life; and)Tj
T*(probably hardly had a Bible in your hands during all that period.  You)Tj
T*(must have forgotten the contents of the book, and you may not have space)Tj
T*(to search it now.  Could it be hurtful to send for some one--some)Tj
T*(minister of any denomination, it does not matter which--to explain it,)Tj
